The Elizabeth Arkham Asylum for the Criminally Insane , typically called Arkham Asylum or simply Arkham -LRB- -LSB- ˈɑrkəm -RSB- -RRB- , is a fictional psychiatric hospital appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics , commonly in stories featuring the superhero Batman .
Arkham Asylum first appeared in Batman # 258 -LRB- October 1974 -RRB- , written by Dennis O'Neil with art by Irv Novick .
Arkham Asylum serves as a psychiatric hospital for the Gotham City area and houses many patients who are criminally insane .
Arkham 's high-profile patients are often from Batman 's rogues gallery , such as the Joker , Two-Face , Poison Ivy , the Riddler , Harley Quinn , Clayface , Mad Hatter , Killer Croc , Mr. Freeze , and Scarecrow .